					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="2303803"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1527717469 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">30 May 2018 21:57</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3818367">
									

<blockquote>
<p>Fair enough, but those are written as informative, usually.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Except Information Breach just doesn't do that. It's not who they are. They're already established in the canon as a biased anti-Foundation source of current events. Brandon Walkers doesn't care if pro-Foundation people read his tone as uninformative, because he's a shit-stirrer anyway and doesn't mind if he comes off as antagonistic &#8212; he has the following to get away with it, because a lot of people hate the Foundation and don't blink twice at opinion takes on events relating to them.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The lead should be be unburied. Your first sentence should be the worst new thing the foundation has done.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The worst new thing the Foundation has done is hide their ownership of South Coast Paper and get sued for it, and that <em>is</em> what the first sentence is about, as well as the headline.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>It's written like a story, not a news/propaganda article. It's a good story.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I'm thinking that you think the collapsible prose sections are supposed to be interpreted as written by the reporter. The news article is what you see without clicking anything; if you read the whole thing without clicking the collapsibles, it's a news article, and the collapsibles are just normal sentences that happen to be in red text color. If you click the collapsibles, you get a four-part tale about the same stuff the news article is about, except behind-the-scenes. This format has functioned pretty seamlessly in my other Broken Masquerade works, with this being the first time someone's held issue with the formatting, so I'm not sure what you would want changed.</p>

							</div>

								
