															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/petrograd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(455145); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=455145&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182126" alt="Petrograd" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=455145)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/petrograd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(455145); return false;" >Petrograd</a></span> <span class="odate time_1529224871 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">17 Jun 2018 08:41</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3838608">
									

<p>I feel like most of my critiques are about the lawsuit, but that's <em>definitely</em> not important.</p>
<p>&#8230; Fuck it, here they are anyway:</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>- For a wingnut pro se case, it definitely scans, but it might've been more fun for other folks (and still realistic) if it was crazier.<br />
- The dollar amount felt really low.<br />
- The Foundation seemed to be taking it a bit too seriously, for what it is.</p>
<p>That said, I'm absolutely no kind of expert, I've just been down some weird YouTube rabbit-holes lately.<br />
&#8212;-</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>The last twist was kind of predictable and I think their plan with the reporter was pretty half-baked, but that's more them being bad people than bad writing.</p>
<p>None of that really matters. Most importantly, I love the character work and worldbuilding to death.</p>
<p>+1</p>

							</div>

								
