					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="2303803"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1529248533 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">17 Jun 2018 15:15</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3839036">
									

<blockquote>
<p>The dollar amount felt really low.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>It was, and it's my bad for forgetting to convey that this was intentional on the plaintiff's part. They weren't after the money, and as such they chose low numbers; they just felt it necessary/a public service to make a scene and bring negative publicity to the Foundation through use of the court system (since that's one of the only places where the Foundation can't just erase what they don't want people to know).</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The Foundation seemed to be taking it a bit too seriously, for what it is.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>And relatedly, they're not really taking the case or the money seriously, they're taking the negative publicity seriously. But like I said, that's an element under the surface that I kind of neglected to make clear, so I'll probably make some edits when the contest is over. Thanks for pointing it out, and I'm glad you liked it overall!</p>

							</div>

								
					
